53.5	Manual_of_Style	Style guide	A style guide or style manual is a set of standards for the writing and design of documents, either for general use or for a specific publication, organization or field. The implementation of a style guide provides uniformity in style and formatting of a document.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/80/GiraffeProjectStandardsManual.png/220px-GiraffeProjectStandardsManual.png
